description:
tensorflow/datasets is a library of datasets ready to use with tensorflow.
tensorflow/datasets is a library of public datasets ready to use with
tensorflow. each dataset definition contains the logic necessary to download and
prepare the dataset, as well as to read it into a model using the
`tf.data.dataset` api.

usage outside of tensorflow is also supported.

see the readme on github for further documentation.

documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) page for the package `tfds-nightly` version 4.9.4.dev202403050044, released on March 5, 2024. It's a library of datasets ready to use with TensorFlow, supporting Python version 3.10 and above. The package is in beta development status, intended for developers and those in science/research, and is licensed under the Apache Software License (Apache 2.0). The page includes a warning for users with unsupported browsers (IE9 and below) and notes that some features may not work without JavaScript. It provides installation instructions, project description, release history, and download files, along with links to the project's homepage and statistics on GitHub.
